President Uhuru Kenyatta has appointed formerÂ Head of Civil Service Amb Francis Muthaura as the chairman of the Kenya Revenue Authority. The president, in a May 23 gazette notice, revoked the appointment of Edward Sambili - a former Central Bank of Kenya deputy governor. The former Planning Permanent Secretary was appointed to the position by Uhuru on October 28, 2016. Uhuru said Muthaura will serve in that post up to October 20 next year. According to the notice, the appointment takes effect from May 22. Click here for the latest political news  